# Security Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph "Security Layers"
        
        Physical[Physical Security]
        Device[Device Security]
        Software[Software Security]
        Cryptographic[Cryptographic Security]
        Protocol[Protocol Security]
        Social[Social Security]
        
    end
    
    Physical --> Device
    Device --> Software
    Software --> Cryptographic
    Cryptographic --> Protocol
    Protocol --> Social
    
    note over Physical: Device theft protection<br/>Drive encryption
    
    note over Device: OS sandboxing<br/>Process isolation
    
    note over Software: Code signing<br/>Update validation
    
    note over Cryptographic: Key hierarchy<br/>Per-ACU encryption
    
    note over Protocol: USP authentication<br/>ZKP verification
    
    note over Social: Phishing protection<br/>Mnemonic security
```

## Threat Model

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph "Threats and Mitigations"
        
        T1[Vault Compromise] --> M1[Client-side encryption, keys never leave device]
        
        T2[Consent Forgery] --> M2[On-chain commitments, ZKP verification]
        
        T3[Buyer Violation] --> M3[Collateral staking, slashing, reputation]
        
        T4[Validator Collusion] --> M4[BFT consensus >2/3 required]
        
        T5[Metadata Leakage] --> M5[Differential privacy, ZK proofs]
        
        T6[Sybil Attacks] --> M6[Proof-of-stake, reputation gating]
        
        T7[Front-Running] --> M7[Encrypted mempool, commit-reveal]
        
    end
    
    style T1 fill:#e94560,stroke:#333,color:#fff
    style M1 fill:#27ae60,stroke:#333,color:#fff
    style T3 fill:#f39c12,stroke:#333,color:#000
    style M3 fill:#27ae60,stroke:#333,color:#fff
```

